# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values.
# `.env.local` (and `.env`) are gitignored and will NOT be committed.
#
# In production (Vercel), set these in:
#   Vercel Dashboard → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# All vars below are SERVER-SIDE only (no VITE_ prefix). They are read by the
# Vercel serverless functions in api/, never exposed to the browser bundle.

# ── Contact form email (SMTP, via Nodemailer) ─────────────────────────────────
# Used by api/send-contact.js to email free-trial submissions to the studio.
#
# Recommended: Gmail SMTP with a Google App Password.
#   1. Sign in to https://myaccount.google.com → Security
#   2. Turn ON 2-Step Verification (required for App Passwords)
#   3. App passwords → create one named "DATA Website" → copy the 16 chars
#   4. Paste into SMTP_PASS below (spaces are fine; Gmail strips them)
#
# Other providers (SendGrid, Mailgun, Brevo, Resend SMTP, on-prem) work the
# same way — just swap host/port/user/pass.
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=dynamicacademyofthearts@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_16_char_google_app_password
# Optional — defaults shown:
SMTP_FROM="DATA Website <dynamicacademyofthearts@gmail.com>"
CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=dynamicacademyofthearts@gmail.com

# ── JackRabbit (server-side only — NO VITE_ prefix) ───────────────────────────
# Used by api/jackrabbit-register.js — creates a Family + Student record when
# a trial form is submitted.
#
# Prerequisites — enable the REST API in JackRabbit admin first:
#   1. Log into app.jackrabbitclass.com
#   2. Settings → Integrations → API (or Account → API Access)
#   3. Enable REST API and copy the API key shown
#
# Local development: run `vercel dev` (NOT `npm run dev`) so api/ routes work.
#   Install Vercel CLI once:  npm i -g vercel
#   Link project once:        vercel link
#   Then develop:             vercel dev
JACKRABBIT_API_KEY=your_jackrabbit_api_key_here
JACKRABBIT_ORG_ID=532199
JACKRABBIT_BASE_URL=https://app.jackrabbitclass.com/jr3.0/openapi
